widgets.title: Top 5 AWS Services by Cost (September 2025)
widgets.description: Visualization of top 5 AWS services by cost for September 2025

widgets.title: Analysis
widgets.content:
**Key Insights:**
- **EC2** is by far your highest expense, accounting for about 60% of your top 5 costs
- **S3 and Savings Plans** have similar costs, each around $3,500
- **ELB and EFS** round out your top 5, with costs around $1,200-1,500 each

Your Savings Plans appear as a cost line item, but they're actually helping reduce your overall EC2 costs through commitment-based discounts. Without these Savings Plans, your EC2 costs would likely be even higher.

Would you like me to provide more detailed analysis of any specific service, such as a breakdown of EC2 costs by instance type or S3 costs by storage class?
